section.programlisting:
public interface Service {
   public void cleanup();
}

public interface BootstrapService extends Service {
    void cleanupAfterBoot();
}

public interface ResourceReference<T> {
    T getInstance();
    void release();
}

section.para:
To allow JPA integration, the JpaServices interface should be implemented. This service
is not required if the implementation of  takes care of
@PersistenceContext injection.

For each

    @Resource injection point
    @PersistenceContext injection point
    @PersistenceUnit injection point
    @EJB injection point
    @WebServiceRef injection point

Weld calls the InjectionServices.registerInjectionTarget() method. That allows the integrator
to validate resource injection points before the application is deployed.

